      <title>Class Balancing cometh</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=SOE&amp;message.id=3888#M3888</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Well sadly not for us, but EQOA gets it at least :smileysad:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;img src="http://newsletters.station.sony.com/templates/eqoa_frontiers_1/images/topRight.gif"&gt;&lt;img src="http://newsletters.station.sony.com/templates/eqoa_frontiers_1/images/left.gif"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Class Balancing&lt;p&gt;Class balancing has been in the works for some time now, and is heading to live servers soon! Here is a peek at some of the class balancing changes the EQOA team has been working on:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Everyone will be able to benefit from some of the stacking changes being made to buffs. Instead of picking which one buff is the most effective, you'll be able to use a variety of different types, including self-buffs, targeted buffs, group or area affect buffs, and buffs that include an illusion change. What this means is that you'll be more appreciative of folks of different specialties in your party, as you'll get different benefits.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the priest category, damage has been improved overall, druid abilities most significantly, clerics are now much more fearful to the undead, and level 60 epic shaman pets are a bit better at their offensive and defensive jobs. Clerics have their path heal recasts decreased, so they can heal more often, as well as recognize improvements to both master classes. Druids have had too many changes to list, but also have seen improvements to both their master classes and some CM cost reductions. Shamans have seen a few CM cost reductions as well.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Our casters have had some significant changes as well. Wizards should notice that their damage is heavily modified by their dexterity stat, and their power should come flowing back to them much more quickly. Magicians and necromancers, with their care and attention, will find their pets improved (but not if left alone for long durations). Necromancers can now increase their healing power with training points into charisma, and can increase their damage by increasing their dexterity. Enchanters will notice that they have a whole lot more ways to give their party power (directly related to the stacking changes) as well as having their charming abilities improved. Alchemists will find that their potion making skills have improved to casting 3 potions at a time, and much, much more.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tank classes overall will be receiving an upgrade to their strength modifier to taunt, smoothing out their buff lines and generally increasing the durations overall, and we're looking into each class to make sure they are effective at their jobs in the ways that their classes should be. Paladins will enjoy changes to heals to make them more useful while tanking, the undead proc line has been upgraded, as well as some other class defining abilities. Shadowknights should enjoy significant increases in most of their &amp;quot;tap&amp;quot; lines as well as improved damage by decreasing the resistance to some abilities. Warriors will enjoy a bit of increased damage in their special abilities, and many abilities scale more appropriately while you level up.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Melee classes have been improved overall to allow their statistics to more significantly affect their damage output, and improving the class specific abilities that make them unique. Rogues can enjoy significant reduction to the recasts of many of their damage dealing abilities, as well as the revamp of some that don't make much sense (Assassinate, Caltrops, and more). Monks' bodies are more like the temples they should be, with increases in their healing capabilities, and increases in their ability to modify their stats with Class Mastery points (namely, hit points, AC, and power). Rangers should be able to make more use of their bows if they have chosen the bow path, and have seen improvements to both their offensive and defensive capabilities Bards will enjoy the stacking changes which will allow them to be an improved support class, and improvements have been made to many of their abilities, rewarding them with increased effectiveness with attention to their stats.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Again, these are just a few of the many changes we've been working on. For more&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
