   &lt;td **SMURF**"padding: 0px 20px; background-color: rgb(229, 213, 177);" valign="top"&gt;&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
      &#xD;
&#xD;
    &lt;span **SMURF**"font-family: georgia,serif; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 12px; line-height: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; color: rgb(63, 28, 0);"&gt;&lt;h3&gt;Class Balancing&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Class&#xD;
balancing has been in the works for some time now, and is heading to&#xD;
live servers soon! Here is a peek at some of the class balancing&#xD;
changes the EQOA team has been working on:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Everyone will be able&#xD;
to benefit from some of the stacking changes being made to buffs.&#xD;
Instead of picking which one buff is the most effective, you'll be able&#xD;
to use a variety of different types, including self-buffs, targeted&#xD;
buffs, group or area affect buffs, and buffs that include an illusion&#xD;
change. What this means is that you'll be more appreciative of folks of&#xD;
different specialties in your party, as you'll get different benefits.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In&#xD;
the priest category, damage has been improved overall, druid abilities&#xD;
most significantly, clerics are now much more fearful to the undead,&#xD;
and level 60 epic shaman pets are a bit better at their offensive and&#xD;
defensive jobs. Clerics have their path heal recasts decreased, so they&#xD;
can heal more often, as well as recognize improvements to both master&#xD;
classes. Druids have had too many changes to list, but also have seen&#xD;
improvements to both their master classes and some CM cost reductions.&#xD;
Shamans have seen a few CM cost reductions as well.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Our casters&#xD;
have had some significant changes as well. Wizards should notice that&#xD;
their damage is heavily modified by their dexterity stat, and their&#xD;
power should come flowing back to them much more quickly. Magicians and&#xD;
necromancers, with their care and attention, will find their pets&#xD;
improved (but not if left alone for long durations). Necromancers can&#xD;
now increase their healing power with training points into charisma,&#xD;
and can increase their damage by increasing their dexterity. Enchanters&#xD;
will notice that they have a whole lot more ways to give their party&#xD;
power (directly related to the stacking changes) as well as having&#xD;
their charming abilities improved. Alchemists will find that their&#xD;
potion making skills have improved to casting 3 potions at a time, and&#xD;
much, much more.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Tank classes overall will be receiving an&#xD;
upgrade to their strength modifier to taunt, smoothing out their buff&#xD;
lines and generally increasing the durations overall, and we're looking&#xD;
into each class to make sure they are effective at their jobs in the&#xD;
ways that their classes should be. Paladins will enjoy changes to heals&#xD;
to make them more useful while tanking, the undead proc line has been&#xD;
upgraded, as well as some other class defining abilities. Shadowknights&#xD;
should enjoy significant increases in most of their "tap" lines as well&#xD;
as improved damage by decreasing the resistance to some abilities.&#xD;
Warriors will enjoy a bit of increased damage in their special&#xD;
abilities, and many abilities scale more appropriately while you level&#xD;
up.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Melee classes have been improved overall to allow their&#xD;
statistics to more significantly affect their damage output, and&#xD;
improving the class specific abilities that make them unique. Rogues&#xD;
can enjoy significant reduction to the recasts of many of their damage&#xD;
dealing abilities, as well as the revamp of some that don't make much&#xD;
sense (Assassinate, Caltrops, and more). Monks' bodies are more like&#xD;
the temples they should be, with increases in their healing&#xD;
capabilities, and increases in their ability to modify their stats with&#xD;
Class Mastery points (namely, hit points, AC, and power). Rangers&#xD;
should be able to make more use of their bows if they have chosen the&#xD;
bow path, and have seen improvements to both their offensive and&#xD;
defensive capabilities Bards will enjoy the stacking changes which will&#xD;
allow them to be an improved support class, and improvements have been&#xD;
made to many of their abilities, rewarding them with increased&#xD;
effectiveness with attention to their stats.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Again, these are just a few of the many changes we've been working on. For more details, please visit our forums!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;&lt;hr size="2" width="100%"&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
